# v0.5.0 — 2026-06-10 — benoitcayladbx

## Fix #48: R2RML relationship URIs use the class label instead of the entity name

**Context**: GitHub issue [#48](https://github.com/databrickslabs/ontobricks/issues/48). In the
Digital Twin graph view, relationships between entities were never rendered in Filter → Expand
mode: only `rdf:type` assertions and datatype-property triples came back, and the BFS expansion
reported `expanded_count == initial_count` (no neighbours discovered). Root cause was a URI
namespace mismatch in the R2RML generator. `_add_entity_mapping` builds entity subject URIs from
the **local name of the ontology class URI** (`{base}{localName}/{id}`), whereas
`_resolve_class_name` — used by `_add_relationship_mapping` for the subject/object templates —
prioritised the **`ontology_class_label`**. When a class label differs from the local name of its
class URI, entity triples and relationship triples were written to two different URI namespaces and
were therefore never linked in the graph.

**Changes**:
1. `src/back/core/w3c/r2rml/R2RMLGenerator.py` — extracted a single shared helper
   `_entity_uri_name(class_uri, class_label, table)` that reproduces the entity subject-URI naming
   rule (local name of the class URI, else label, else table) as the **single source of truth** for
   the class-name segment of an entity URI. `_add_entity_mapping` now calls it (replacing the inline
   duplicate). `_resolve_class_name` now, for a matched entity, returns `_entity_uri_name(...)` using
   the matched entity's own `ontology_class` / `ontology_class_label` / table — guaranteeing the
   relationship subject/object URIs land byte-for-byte in the same namespace as the entity URIs. The
   former Priority 1 (entity label first) was the bug and is removed; the no-entity-matched fallback
   path (resolved URI → config label → class URI → table) is preserved unchanged.
2. `tests/units/mapping/test_r2rml_generator.py` — added
   `test_relationship_uris_match_entity_uris_when_label_differs`, a regression test for #48 where the
   class URI local names (`Cust`, `Ord`) deliberately differ from the labels (`Customer`, `Order`).
   It asserts that both entity and relationship templates use the `Cust`/`Ord` namespace and that the
   label namespace (`Customer/`, `Order/`) never appears.

**Modified files**:
- `src/back/core/w3c/r2rml/R2RMLGenerator.py`
- `tests/units/mapping/test_r2rml_generator.py`

**Test result**: `python -m pytest tests/units` -> **2266 passed, 15 skipped**. Targeted
`tests/units/mapping tests/units/dtwin` -> 262 passed. (`tests/property` skipped: `hypothesis` not
installed in this env — nightly-only.)
